<item>
            <title>[LU-8885] zconf_mount_clients() defect</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8885</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&quot;zconf_mount_clients()&quot; does not check that lustre fs is mounted on $mnt,&lt;br/&gt;
it just checks &quot;mount | grep -c $mnt&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
In case if nfs client is mounted on $mnt zconf_mount_clients() does not try to mount lustre client at all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Starting client redpill-client02,redpill-client03,redpill-client04,redpill-client05,redpill-client06,redpill-client07,redpill-client08.ext:  -o user_xattr,flock 172.18.1.3@o2ib:/fs1 /mnt/fs1
Started clients redpill-client02,redpill-client03,redpill-client04,redpill-client05,redpill-client06,redpill-client07,redpill-client08.ext: 
172.16.200.1:/mnt/fs1 on /mnt/fs1 type nfs (rw,nfsvers=3,addr=172.16.200.1)
172.16.200.1:/mnt/fs1 on /mnt/fs1 type nfs (rw,nfsvers=3,addr=172.16.200.1)
172.16.200.1:/mnt/fs1 on /mnt/fs1 type nfs (rw,nfsvers=3,addr=172.16.200.1)
172.16.200.1:/mnt/fs1 on /mnt/fs1 type nfs (rw,nfsvers=3,addr=172.16.200.1)
172.16.200.1:/mnt/fs1 on /mnt/fs1 type nfs (rw,nfsvers=3,addr=172.16.200.1)
172.16.200.1:/mnt/fs1 on /mnt/fs1 type nfs (rw,nfsvers=3,addr=172.16.200.1)
172.16.200.1:/mnt/fs1 on /mnt/fs1 type nfs (rw,nfsvers=3,addr=172.16.200.1)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


</description>
